RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCKY LOCKETT broke alertly and established the early advantage, was well rated through the backstretch run while prompted, set moderate fractions to the quarter marker, shook free in the drive, kept to task in deep stretch and held in a drive at the finish to prove best. SPORTS FOR WOMEN took back off of the moderate early pace, was roused two wide nearing the quarter marker, raced three wide into the stretch, finished well inside of the furlong marker, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and was up in time to secure the place. I'M GONNA SHINE was forwardly placed into the first turn, attended to the pace into the backstretch run, pressed LUCKY LOCKETT to the far turn, kept close attendance to the pacesetter to the quarter pole, lost ground in upper stretch, weakened in the final sixteenth and was outfinished for the place, while clear of the rest for the show. THE RIVER MANGITA was unhurried, improved position while four wide on the far turn, was unable to impact the leaders in deep stretch and offered a mild late rally. NOMI LACKEE was prominent into the first turn, raced close to the moderate fractions through the backstretch run, lost position while saving ground on the far turn and gave way in the stretch drive. LOOKOUT PASS chased the moderate pace, raced outside of rivals along the backstretch run, came three wide into the second turn, dropped back at the quarter marker and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 80. Claiming Purse 13400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUE SERA SIR RALPH broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, set modest fractions through the backstretch run while well handled, showed the way to the quarter marker, quickened in upper stretch and drew clear at the furlong marker, was kept to steady urging in the late stages and drew off in deep stretch to be much the best. PORT O' CALL was allowed to settle while not far back, raced three wide into the far turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, could not muster the needed late response, was outkicked by the winner in the drive and ran on to secure second. DANNY MICHAEL was hard to load, brushed with CARSON'S LEGACY at the start and was off a step slowly, was unhurried through the backstretch run, raced three wide into the stretch, finished evenly in the final furlong and was clear for third at the finish. MONEY MUNCHER chased the moderate fractions from the inside, ran evenly to the furlong pole and gave way late. CARSON'S LEGACY brushed with DANNY MICHAEL at the start, stalked the early pace then advanced to prompt the pacesetter along the backstretch run, kept attendance to QUE SERA SIR RALPH to the quarter pole, lost ground in the drive and tired in the final stages.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLOSSOMING took back off of the decent early pace, raced in the clear while outside of rivals along the backstretch run, slipped to the two path entering the far turn, came in a bit tight in upper stretch, found room approaching the furlong marker, loomed at mid-stretch, kicked clear heading to the sixteenth-marker and drew off under hand urging in the final stages. PRANCIN N THE PARK settled in the early going while not far back, maintained position through the backstretch run, gained ground while two wide on the second turn, vied for the lead with BLOSSOMING to the furlong marker, was no match for the winner in the final stages and was best of the rest. RELUCTANT was caught wide into the first turn, took back off of the decent pace and tracked through the backstretch run, mounted a three wide bid to come within aim at the quarter pole, chased to mid-stretch, weakened in the late stages and held for third. CREATING MEMORIES took back in the early stages, improved position along the backstretch run, saved ground into the far turn, steadied while in tight quarters midway through the turn, lost position in upper stretch and gave way in the drive. LADY BLACKBIRD broke alertly and was sent to establish the early lead, drifted three wide into the first turn and carried out a rival, showed speed through the backstretch run, was pressed to the quarter marker, overtaken in upper stretch, chased to the furlong pole and faded in the final stages. PETE'S INFERNO was forwardly placed into the first turn, was carried four wide by the drifting pacesetter early, kept close attendance through the backstretch run, was tiring on the run into the far turn, steadied while shuffled back nearing the quarter marker, lost contact in upper stretch and was not persevered with in the drive.

EL CHARRO CHAMP showed good early speed and disputed the pace while between rivals, raced three wide into the turn, was overtaken by GENTLEMAN'S SECRET midway through the turn, chased that foe to mid-stretch, battled with AWE for the place spot in the final furlong and just missed for second, while clear of the rest for third. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since January 15 All owed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHERILINDA broke well then tracked just behind and to the outside of MIRACLE IN MOTION while well in hand through moderate fractions, got on even terms at the top of he stretch while still under wraps, responded when roused in the stretch and held on while drifting out in the final sixteenth. ZABAVA last away, reserved near the rear of the field to the far turn while racing three wide, began a sustained bid passing the nine-sixteenths pole, made a sweeping move around the far turn while three to four wide, continued the rally through the stretch and was gaining on the winner but ran out of ground. MIRACLE IN MOTION hustled to the front, attempted to slow down the pace but was pressed from behind by SHERLINDA to the top of the lane, responded when challenged in the stretch but was unable to match strides in the late stages. SHANGHAI MIST outrun then shuffled back to the rear of the field going into the clubhouse turn, worked to the outside for clear run into the far turn, launched a four wide bid that carried six wide into the stretch and finished up well while never a serious threat. GOING TO SHABOOMS came away well but was caught wide into the first turn, advanced through the turn to gain a good tracking position three wide down the backstretch, loomed a threat turning for home but stalled and finished evenly. DR WYSONG was not asked for speed early and saved ground while racing mid-pack early, began to improve position down the backstretch, lost some ground when the pace quickened on the far turn but re-rallied a bit but was unable to improve from that point while getting leaned on by TEAM CONCEPT down the lane. TEAM CONCEPT got off a step slow, was boxed in through the first turn and shuffled back to near the rear of the field, moved up into contention in tandem with and to the outside of DR WYSONG, dropped back some on the far turn then was unable to improve position, keeping that foe in tight quarters while lugging in through the stretch.
